data.enText: the pleasant smell that sth has

data.chText: 空气中弥漫着野花的芬芳。
data.enText: The air was filled with the scent of wild flowers.
These flowers have no scent.

data.chText: （人的）气味，气息；（动物留下的）臭迹，遗臭
data.enText: the smell that a person or an animal leaves behind and that other animals such as dogs can follow

data.chText: 狗准是闻不到她的气味了。
data.enText: The dogs must have lost her scent.
a liquid with a pleasant smell that you wear on your skin to make it smell nice
a bottle of scent
the feeling that sth is present or is going to happen very soon
The scent of victory was in the air.
put/throw sb off the scent

data.chText: 使失去线索；摆脱追踪者；使迷失寻找方向
data.enText: to do sth to stop sb from finding you or discovering sth
on the scent (of sth)

data.chText: 已获得线索；已掌握蛛丝马迹
data.enText: close to discovering sth
to find sth by using the sense of smell
The dog scented a rabbit.
to begin to feel that sth exists or is about to happen
The press could scent a scandal.

data.chText: 到那时，队员已经预感到即将获胜了。
data.enText: By then, the team was scenting victory.
to give sth a particular, pleasant smell

data.chText: 夜空中弥漫着玫瑰花香。
data.enText: Roses scented the night air.

ex.enText: The rose gave off a sweet smell.

ex.chText: 油漆味几天后就会消失。
ex.enText: The smell of the paint will pass off in a few days.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指任何通过嗅觉器官感受到的气味，可以是好闻的或难闻的。

ex.chText: 空气中满是玫瑰花的香味。
ex.enText: The air is full of the fragrance of roses.

ex.chText: 丁香散发出芬芳的香味。
ex.enText: The lilac gave off a sweet fragrance.

synonyms.bx: 指怡人的气味，尤指鲜花等散发出的香气。

ex.chText: 这种液体有种特别难闻的气味。
ex.enText: This liquid has an extremely unpleasant odour.

ex.chText: 这种食品散发出叫人难以忍受的气味。
ex.enText: This kind of food gave off an unbearable odour.

ex.chText: 它会明确地告诉我们在你的房间里有什么气味。
ex.enText: It will tell us specifically what odours are found in your room.

synonyms.bx: 指易于辨别的强烈气味，多指难闻的臭味，常用于科技文章中。

ex.enText: The scent of lemons filled the hall.
The breeze wafted with scents of the grass.

ex.chText: 猎犬循着臭迹追踪猎物。
ex.enText: The hounds followed their game by scent.

synonyms.bx: 指某物的香味，或人、动物身上散发出的气味。

ex.chText: 空气中充满了烂鱼的臭味。
ex.enText: The air is full of the stink of decayed fish.

ex.chText: 你可以闻到死尸的臭味。
ex.enText: You can smell the stink of the dead body.

ex.chText: 那臭味都快把我熏死了。
ex.enText: The stink nearly blew my head off.

tr: any property detected by the olfactory system
an odor left in passing by which a person or animal can be traced
a distinctive odor that is pleasant

example: The dog nosed out the drugs

tr: cause to smell or be smelly

value.def: The scent of something is the pleasant smell that it has.

example.ex: Flowers are chosen for their scent as well as their look.
example.tran: 选花不仅要观其形还要闻其香。

value.def: If something scents a place or thing, it makes it smell pleasant.

example.tran: 空气中弥漫着茉莉花香。

example.ex: Scent your drawers and wardrobe with your favourite aromas.
example.tran: 用你最喜欢的香味熏香你的抽屉和衣柜。

value.def: Scent is a liquid which women put on their necks and wrists to make themselves smell nice.

example.tran: 她在身上擦了一点香水。

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 perfume

value.def: The scent of a person or animal is the smell that they leave and that other people sometimes follow when looking for them.

example.ex: A police dog picked up the murderer's scent...
example.tran: 一只警犬嗅出了凶手的气味。

example.ex: Many kinds of insect find their mates by scent.
example.tran: 许多昆虫通过气味找到交配对象。

value.tran: (人的)气味，气息;(动物的)臭迹，遗臭

value.def: When an animal scents something, it becomes aware of it by smelling it.
If you scent a situation, you feel that it is going to happen.

example.ex: Republicans from Pennsylvania and New York are scenting victory.
example.tran: 来自宾夕法尼亚州和纽约州的共和党人预感到胜利在望。
